        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued July 8 at 3:28PM EDT until July 8 at 4:15PM EDT by NWS Columbia SC</headline>
        <description>SVRCAE

The National Weather Service in Columbia has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
Southwestern Burke County in east central Georgia...

* Until 415 PM EDT.

* At 328 PM EDT, a severe thunderstorm was located near Burke County
Airport, or 8 miles south of Waynesboro, and is nearly stationary.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and quarter size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Hail damage to vehicles is expected. Expect wind damage
to trees and powerlines.

* Locations impacted include...
Waynesboro, Midville, Burke County Airport, Di-
Lane Wildlife Management Area, Magruder, and Rosier.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
